  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6508.05 sitting above the GEX flip at 6471 in a BREAKOUT regime, dealers are aggressively short gamma and will amplify moves by buying this rally and selling any dips. The massive -6840M negative gamma wall at 6475 creates a critical support level where dealers become aggressive buyers, while the +1401M positive gamma at 6525 represents strong resistance where dealers will sell rallies.\n\nExpect continued volatile trending action with dealers providing fuel rather than stability - any push toward 6525 will face increasing dealer selling pressure, but a break below 6500 (-1680M) accelerates dealer selling toward the key 6475 support level where buying should emerge.\n\n**Key strikes: Watch 6475 support (major dealer buying) and 6525 resistance (dealer selling pressure).**",
